<h2 id="honest-assessment">The Honest Assessment</h2>

<p>Ghana's agricultural sector beyond cocoa offers genuine opportunities for disciplined operators. The macro environment is the most favourable in years: inflation at 3.3%, policy rate at 14% (down from 29%), cedi stable, and GDP growing at 6.0%.</p>

<p>But "genuine opportunity" does not mean "easy money." Every sub-sector has specific constraints that will kill underprepared operators. The scoring methodology is designed to be honest: a 6.65 is not a 7.0, and the difference matters when you are committing your savings.</p>

